# Module Docstring Format

**Apply this whenever you add or edit a module docstring** (the top-level
docstring in a Python file). Referenced by `docstrings-include-module.mdc`.

Module docstrings must use this structure:

1. **First line**: The module name (e.g. the dotted path or logical name).
2. **Second line**: An underline of `=` characters, same length as line 1.
3. **Blank line**.
4. **Description**: One or more lines describing what the module does.

## Template

```python
"""
$module_name
$underline_same_length_as_module_name

$description
"""
```

## Examples

```python
# ❌ BAD — no title/underline, only description
"""Run docstring/signature checks on module functions and classes."""

# ❌ BAD — underline length does not match module name
"""
docsig._check
=========

Run checks on module functions and classes.
"""

# ✅ GOOD
"""
docsig._check
=============

Run docstring/signature checks on module functions and classes.
"""
```

Keep the description to a single sentence when possible. Wrap long
description lines so each line (including indent) is at most 72 characters
(see `docstring-line-length.mdc`).
